

1. What is Google Sheet and how is it different from Excel?



| Aspect        | Google Sheets                 | Excel                     |

| ------------- | ----------------------------- | ------------------------- |

| Access        | Browser/mobile, always online | Desktop app + web version |

| Cost          | Free                          | $6.99+/month              |

| Collaboration | Real-time multi-user editing  | OneDrive needed           |

| Row Limit     | 10M cells total               | 1M+ rows/sheet            |

| Speed         | Slower for big data           | Faster processing         |

| Formulas      | 200+ functions                | 450+ advanced             |



Best: Sheets for teams, Excel for data scientists.​







2. How can multiple people work together in a single sheet?



	Real-time editing with colored cursors showing who's typing:



Steps:



1.    Click Share (top-right)
   
2.    Add emails or copy link
   
3.    Set permissions: Viewer/Commenter/Editor
   
4.    Chat panel for discussion
   
5.    @mentions notify people



Features:



✅ Live changes appear instantly

✅ Version history (File → Version history)

✅ Offline mode available

✅ Mobile editing







3. What are some commonly used formulas in Google Sheet?



| Category  | Formula                  | Example         |

| --------- | ------------------------ | --------------- |

| Totals    | =SUM(A1:A10)             | Add range       |

| Average   | =AVERAGE(B1:B5)          | Mean value      |

| Condition | =IF(C1>50,"Pass","Fail") | Logic test      |

| Text      | =JOIN(" ",A1,B1)         | "Rahul Kumar"   |

| Today     | =TODAY()                 | 2/18/2026       |

| Count     | =COUNTA(D1:D10)          | Non-empty cells |







4. How can you protect a specific cell or range in a Google Sheet?



	Lock formulas while allowing data entry:



Steps:



1.    Select range (formulas like C1:C10)
   
2.    Data → Protect sheets and ranges
   
3.    Add rule → Set permissions
   
4.    Choose: "Only you" or "Custom list"
   
5.    Save - others get warning/edit blocked



Example: Protect totals column, free data columns.







5. What are the benefits of using Google Sheet in daily work?



    Free forever + auto-backup



    Team access anywhere (phone/laptop)



    No install - just browser



    Templates for budgets/projects



    Google Forms → auto-fill sheets



    IMPORTRANGE between files



    Apps Script for automation



Perfect for: Small business, students, remote teams, daily trackers.



Excel better for: Financial modeling, huge datasets, VBA macros.​

